Mechanic Shop Management System
Design Document

1. Overview
This application was created to help manage a mechanic shop using a Java console program connected to a MariaDB database.

2. Objectives
- Store vehicle records
- Manage inventory parts
- Generate customer invoices
- Practice OOP and database programming

3. Program Structure

Packages:
- ui
- database
- models
- exceptions

4. Main Classes

Main.java
Starts the program and displays main menu.

VehicleMenu.java
Handles vehicle menu options.

InventoryMenu.java
Handles parts and invoice options.

VehicleDAO.java
Database operations for vehicles.

PartDAO.java
Database operations for parts.

InvoiceDAO.java
Database operations for invoices.

DatabaseManager.java
Creates database connection.

Models:
- Vehicle
- Car
- Truck
- Part
- Invoice
- Inventory
- ServiceRecord

Exceptions:
- InvalidInputException
- InsufficientPartsException
- DuplicateVehicleException
- VehicleNotFoundException

5. Database Tables
vehicle(id, make, model)
part(id, name, quantity, price)

6. Input Validation
The program checks:
- invalid menu choices
- text instead of numbers
- negative values
- empty text fields
- missing records

7. OOP Concepts Used
- Encapsulation
- Inheritance
- Polymorphism
- Exception Handling

8. Conclusion
The project successfully demonstrates Java programming, menus, validation, and database integration.